# What Exactly Is a Variable?

A variable is a named location used to store information.

Think of a variable as a labeled notebook page.

Imagine your notebook contains:

```text
Page 1 → Physics Formulae

Page 2 → Chemistry Formulae

Page 3 → Mathematics Formulae
```

Because each page has a label, finding information becomes easy.

Variables work similarly.

Example:

```python
name = "Harshita"
```

Visualization:

```text
name
 │
 ▼
"Harshita"
```

The label is:

```text
name
```

The stored information is:

```text
Harshita
```

---

