# Your First Variable

Consider:

```python
college = "IIIT"
```

Do not read this as:

> College equals IIIT

Instead read it as:

> Store "IIIT" inside a variable called college.

Visualization:

```text
college
   │
   ▼
 "IIIT"
```

The variable is the label.

The value is the information.

---

# Why Is It Called a Variable?

Imagine your semester CGPA.

After first semester:

```text
CGPA = 7.8
```

After second semester:

```text
CGPA = 8.2
```

After third semester:

```text
CGPA = 8.6
```

The label:

```text
CGPA
```

remains the same.

Only the value changes.

In Python:

```python
cgpa = 7.8

cgpa = 8.2

cgpa = 8.6
```

The value can vary.

Hence the name:

**Variable**

